<br>
I don't think anyone has completed any of the quests yet in new ST, so people are still unsure if there is anything worthwhile there.  They all seem relatively long, though -- collect drops from all across the zone and then hand them in.<br>
<br>
I don't think any guild on FV is ready to take on the new ST and from a pure risk v. reward aspect, there is no reason to do so.  New ST is a lot more work for roughly the same or poorer items.  The only reason to do the wakeup, IMHO, is to see if VI did a new nifty transition script.  If they did, it would be a really fun thing to experience.  Well, the new ST is a fun zone-crawl type of raid, but when I do that much work I like to see nice stuff dropping for people, not &quot;sorry, pass, I have better&quot;.  NTOV is a lot more fun and a lot more rewarding than new ST. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#A62A2A>- </font><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie>Firiona Vie</a><font color=#A62A2A> - </font><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1>Firiona Vie General Chat</a> <font color=#A62A2A> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 7.0.8<br>Copyright ©1999-2002 ezboard, Inc.<br>Accelerated By <a href=http://www.wbs.com/ezboard.html>JXEL</a></center></body></html>  

